---
title: Rosemary Chicken with Mashed Potatoes & Roasted Carrots
description: These, friends, are not your average pork chops. Our chefs gave ‘em a steak-like treatment, transforming the everyday protein into something above and beyond. The chops are seared to perfection, then drizzled with an ultra-savory, rosemary-flecked pan sauce. The sides? Just as impressive. We’re serving up creamy mashed potatoes and roasted carrots and red onion wedges to round everything out.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/rosemary-demi-glace-pork-chops-76848792.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/658c62c8529576b8aa46b0c7.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 430 mg
author: Sara Heilman
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/rosemary-chicken-658c62c8529576b8aa46b0c7
course: main course
cuisine: North America
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Toss carrots and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of oil, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

While veggies roast, dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. (TIP: For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.) Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (3 tsp for 4 servings).

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add minced onion and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%TBSP} until melted.

Return pot with drained potatoes to medium-low heat. Add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @butter{1%TBSP}. Mash with #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and veggies between plates. Top chicken with sauce and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.